I"j<p>I’ve spent some time learning/working on this website using Jekyll and Bootstrap 4. Through a mixture of documentation, trial and error, and perseverance, I at least have a basic layout of what details I want to display on this site. However, I did get caught up on one details; how to highlight the navbar link depending on the current page. I figured I would show how I did to impart this knowledge to fellow front end web developer learners. I assume the reader has some experience with Jekyll already.</p>

<p>The website is organized as follows:</p>
<ul>
  <li>_layouts
    <ul>
      <li>default.html</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>post.html</li>
  <li>project.html</li>
  <li>_includes</li>
  <li>footer.html</li>
  <li>header.html</li>
  <li>navbar.html</li>
  <li>_data</li>
  <li>navbar.yml</li>
  <li>projects.yml</li>
  <li>index.html</li>
  <li>…other files</li>
</ul>

<p>Layouts hold default.html, which uses the header, navbar, and fotoer in _includes. Here is a code snippet from navbar.html.</p>

